Did you know prismacolor discontinued two of their light purple colored pencils? Lilac pc956 and lavender pc934 have been discontinued so I looked through all of the colored pencils I owned to find good duplicates. I wanted the pencils to be available open stock and also to be soft and wax based so they'd be similar to prismacolor pencils. 

Here's what I found: 

Creative Mark Cezanne color pencils at Jerry's Artarama in color periwinkle number 027 was a good match for lavender pc934. They're available in a box of six for $3.99 at Jerrysartarama.com. 

Arteza's lilac colored pencil (old number A062, new number A408) was a great match for prismacolors lilac pc596. You can find a box of 3 for $5.99 at arteza.com

I hope this helps you find substitutions for your favorite colors. I will have a more in-depth video soon on my YouTube channel the frugal crafter.

I pick up this sketchbook when I want an adventure. I started it at the beginning of 2020. The sizing has gone bad, there will be no smooth watercolor gradients (or any blending at all) here. It grabs paint in some areas and resists it in others. Pens either feather wildly or skip completely on its pages. Sometimes I neglect it for months. I've even left it outside a time or two. There are bumps and flecks in the paper which curls at the hint of moisture (a quirky surprise in a watercolor sketchbook!) Other people might chuck this sketchbook and move on to one of the dozens of others waiting in the wings but I am excited by the inconsistent beauty in the flaws that I am responsible for.

PSA: Don't leave your sketchbooks outside, the sizing can go bad. Also, don't give up if something isn't perfect. The beauty is in the flaws.

I need to get over the feeling that it's a waste if I don't film a tutorial. A pastime is never a waste if you enjoy doing it.
